@node Rules

                             @{b}@{fg shine}Mauscheln@{ub}@{fg text}


    Mauscheln is a gambling card game that I learned in Oldenburg, Germany.
    And I thought to myself, that it's about time to write this game.
    I hope that all you Amiga users like this game.

           @{" 3 player rules " link 3Player}.. not implemented
           @{" 4 player rules " link 4Player}
           @{" 5 player rules " link 5Player}.. not implemented
@endnode
@node 3Player
@title "3 player rules"

    Mauscheln doesn't support 3 player rules.. and won't.. ain't no fun

    Hardly anyone looses when only 3 play... ain't no fun, because the pot
    hardly ever grows.

    Won't implement... to much work for so less fun
@endnode
@node 5Player
@title "5 player rules""

    Mauscheln doesn't support 5-6 player rule yet... I guess I don't have
    a reason to... sorry

    In this mode everyone is allready scared before seeing the cards.
    Except for the 6th player when he deals the cards.
@endnode
@node 4Player
@title "4 player rules"

                         @{fg shine}New Game...@{fg text}

    Someone is selected to start dealing. How doesn't matter... as long as
    just someone takes the cards and starts shuffling.
    The game is played clockwise..

    Every time when the pot is empty everyone is invited and must play.
    Mauscheln is played until the pot is empty again. Either the players
    decide to quit or the next player invites all and puts a certain amount
    of cash into the pot.

        @{fg shine}Place your money...@{fg text}

    The Macher (Maker) puts 20 Cent in the pot. If @{"Hot game" link Hot Game} (Hot version)
    is played, the maker has to put 40cents in the pot and everybody else
    20 cents.

       @{fg shine}Dealing the cards...@{fg text}

    The maker gives first himself and then the others 2 cards face down.
    The next card is placed face up before the maker.. this card is trump.
    Then again the maker deals himself and then the others 2 cards.

       @{fg shine}Trade...@{fg text}

   	...Click the cards that you want to @{"trade" link Trade}.

    You can trade none to all of your cards and must throw the cards to be
    traded away before you get new ones.
    The maker is the first to trade his cards if needed and becomes the face
    up trump card and must throw one of his 5 cards before the round starts.
    The next player clockwise in turn may trade his cards if needed.

       @{fg shine}Ready to play...@{fg text}

    ...WARNING! You have to @{"whistle" link Whistle} when holding 4 trump cards!


    The goal for the maker is to get at least 2 from 4 hits.
    The goal for the other players is to get at least one hit.
    When invited, at least one player looses and must replace the pot.

    Everyone with 4 trumps in his hand has to whistle. If you forgot to
    whistle before the first card is played, you have to replace the pot and
    others that would of lost, didn't loose!

    The maker starts the round and throws a card. The next player has to
    throw a higher card in the same color if possable. If the next player
    can't play the same color, a trump must be played. If the next player
    can't play trump... throw anything.
    If you win the hit, you come out and throw the next lead card.

    The hits are counted after the round. You will receive 1/4 of the pot
    for every hit. If you lost.. that means not even 1 hit, you have to
    replace the pot.
    The maker needs 2 hits.. if not, replace the pot.
    If the maker didn't even get one hit, everyone gets a "Filzlaus"
    (Feltlouse), which is 10 cents.

                        @{b}Pot is full of money...@{ub}

    ...Click the card symbol to play a @{"new game" link NewGame}.

    The next person in turn deals the cards.

    See place your money.
    See dealing the cards.

    As soon as the face up trump card is dealt, you must tell if you play
    the game, need only one hit or Ace must play

        @{fg shine}Need only one hit...@{fg text}

    If the dealt face up trump is a 7, then the maker only needs one hit
    to win. This doesn't count when invited to an empty pot.

        @{fg shine}Ace must...@{fg text}

    The maker can call "Ace must" if he doesn't like the face up trump card.
    The other players that didn't look into the cards by now have the chance
    to grab the trump card and become the maker.

    If nobody grabed the game, everyone looks if they have the Ace trump
    card. If you have the Ace you must play the game and are the maker. The
    face up trump card is also thrown away and your out of luck.

    See trade
    See ready to play

        @{fg shine}The maker plays the round...@{fg text}

    The others now decide if they want to play along, throw thier cards, play
    along having a "Färbel" or play as the "last" player.

        @{fg shine}Last...@{fg text}

    If nobody's playing against the maker yet, you can try to play as last.
    This means, hope that the others throw away their cards and that you end
    up as the only opponent. But if the next player calls last you are out.
    If one player plays along then of coarse nobody can call last.
    As the last player, you can recieve 5 new cards when throwing all 4 away.
    The 5th card is dealt face up to give everybody a glance to see if you
    recieved a trump.

    See trade
    See ready to play

        @{fg shine}Färbel...@{fg text}

    If all non-trump cards have the same color, you can recieve 4 new cards
    immediatly that are given face up and you must play along. You can trade
    these cards again when it's your turn to trade cards.

    See trade
    See ready to play
@endnode
@node NewGame
@title "New Game..."

    With the small symbol at the bottom left side you can start a new game.
    The game is played until the pot is empty again.
@endnode
@node Trade
@title "Trade..."

    Simply click the cards that you want to trade. These will slide up a
    little bit. If you decide to keep the card, just click it again and the
    card will slide back down.
    
    Last but not least, click the Trade button.
@endnode
@node Hot Game
@title "Hot game..."

    Once in a while a requester pops up after a game and asks if you want to
    play a higher stake. In this case the inviting maker puts 40 cents in
    the pot and all other players 20 cents.
    Thus the pot is started with a dollar. (There's that dollar again)
    
    @{"Play for more" link Big Bucks}... not a Mauscheln (Fiddle) rule
@endnode
@node Big Bucks
@title "Big Bucks..."

    This is not a Mauscheln rule, but simply my idea to play with lot's of
    cash. If you reach certain amounts, you have the chance to play for 10x
    as much. The steps are 
    Normal -,20 Hot Game 1,- Greedy 10,- Big Bucks 100,- Paychecks 1000,-
@endnode
@node Whistle
@title "Whistle by 4 trumps"

    There is an invisable button at the bottom left corner to simulate that
    you whistled. Invisable on purpose to not to remind you that you have to
    whistle.
    
    If you didn't whistle by the time the first card is played you lost and
    must double the pot. No matter how the game ended.
@endnode
@node last
@title "Last opponent..."

    If you are the only opponent and called "last", you can recieve 5 cards
    when trading all 4. Simply click all your cards and press the Trade
    button. Then again click one of the 5 cards to get rid of it.
@endnode
@node Färbel

    A Requestor pops up if you want to play "Färbel" (Colory)
@endnode
@node REKO

    RRiSC (RKP to REKO to ilbm's to Single Cards) is a small tool to help
    get single cards (brush) from RKP or REKO cardsets.
    I didn't feel like rewriting Mauscheln. So I wrote this little helper
    so Mauscheln can also use the REKO arts.
@endnode
@node History
@title "Emerged..."

                                 Mauscheln

      written with      CanDo V3.008    from Inovatronics
      Amiga emulation   WinUAE 0.8.23   from Cloanto
      started on a      ALDI PC ME/XP   sometime in 2005
      finished on a     Medion "AKOYA"  from Aldi Nord
      looked for        REKO things     at REKO Productions
      changed RKP with  ConvertReko     from Deok-Min Yun to REKO
      installed         REKO.datatype   from Dirk Stöcker
      changed REKO with MultiView       to *.ilbm
      changed HAM8 with PersonalPaint   from Cloanto to 256color.ilbm
      wrote a helper    RRiSC           for Mauscheln

